chunk_content: For example, a community site keeps secure and safe records of all key populations tested at that site. This community site has determined it can report on the KP disaggregate in a safe and confidential way. Of the 100 individuals who were identified as KP, and who were tested and received their results (including confirmation of diagnosis) at this site, the community site reports 100 under the appropriate modality (in this case, VCT) AND reports 100 under the KP disaggregate. See Appendix A: Key Population Classification Document, to inform identification of key populations at HTS service delivery. However, reporting of key population disaggregation should be consistent with what is described under the KP_PREV “How to review for data quality” section on mutual exclusivity of an individual who falls under multiple key population categories (e.g., FSW who injects drugs).
